1. *Stop*! Ne prelazi ulicu dok ne budeš siguran da nema vozila. (Stop! Don't cross the street until you're sure there are no vehicles.)
2. Vozač je pritisnuo *stop* dugme da bi zaustavio autobus na stanici. (The driver pressed the *stop* button to stop the bus at the station.)
3. Zbog gužve u saobraćaju, automobil je morao da *stoji* na semaforu nekoliko minuta. (Due to traffic congestion, the car had to *stand* at the traffic light for a few minutes.)
4. Danas smo posetili arheološko nalazište gde smo videli ostatke antičkog *grad*а koji je bio *zaustavljen* u vremenu. (Today we visited an archaeological site where we saw the remains of an ancient *city* that was *stopped* in time.)
5. Potrebno je da *zaustavimo* zagađenje životne sredine kako bismo sačuvali prirodu za buduće generacije. (We need to *stop* environmental pollution to preserve nature for future generations.)
6. Kada su videli policajce, razbojnici su *pokušali da pobegnu*, ali su bili *zaustavljeni* i uhapšeni. (When they saw the police, the robbers *tried to escape*, but they were *stopped* and arrested.)
7. Turisti su *stajali* pored fontane i uživali u lepom vremenu. (The tourists *stood* next to the fountain and enjoyed the nice weather.)
8. *Zaustavi* se malo i odmori, ne moraš sve da završiš odjednom. (Take a *break* and rest for a bit, you don't have to finish everything at once.)